components.name: FormFieldComponent
components.templateData:
<mat-form-field floatLabel="always">
  <mat-label class="watt-label"><ng-content select="watt-label"></ng-content></mat-label>

  <ng-container matPrefix>
    <ng-content select="[wattPrefix]"></ng-content>
  </ng-container>

  <ng-content select="[wattInput]"></ng-content>

  <ng-container matSuffix>
    <ng-content select="[wattSuffix]"></ng-content>
  </ng-container>

  <mat-error class="watt-text-xs">
    <ng-content select="watt-error"></ng-content>
  </mat-error>

  <mat-hint class="watt-text-xs" align="start">
    <ng-content select="watt-hint:not(watt-hint[align='end'])"></ng-content>
  </mat-hint>

  <mat-hint class="watt-text-xs" align="end">
    <ng-content select="watt-hint[align='end']"></ng-content>
  </mat-hint>

  <ng-container *ngIf="beforeViewInit">
    <input matInput class="tmp-mat-field" />
  </ng-container>
</mat-form-field>

components.name: InputComponent
components.template:
<watt-form-field [size]="size">      <watt-label>{{label}}</watt-label>
      <button *ngIf="hasPrefix" wattPrefix aria-label="some meaningful description">
        icon
      </button>
      <input wattInput type="text" maxlength="256" [formControl]="exampleFormControl" [placeholder]="placeholder"/>
      <button *ngIf="hasSuffix" wattSuffix aria-label="some meaningful description">
        icon
      </button>
      <watt-error *ngIf="exampleFormControl.hasError('required')">
      This field is required
      </watt-error>
      <watt-hint *ngIf="hasHint">Some hint</watt-hint>
      <watt-hint *ngIf="hasHint" align="end">{{exampleFormControl.value.length}} / 256</watt-hint>
    </watt-form-field>

components.name: TypographyComponent
components.templateData:
Typography

Font

Open Sans is the typeface used in the Watts Design System.

Type Scale

Font sizes are smaller on mobile and scale up at the md breakpoint to be larger on desktop.

Name Size {{ element.size }} Weight {{ element.weight }} Letter Case {{ element.letterCase }} Letter Spacing {{ element.letterSpacing }} Line Height {{ element.lineHeight }}

* Line height is set to the recommended minimum of 1.5 times the font size by WCAG 2.1.

Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software
distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,
WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.
See the License for the specific language governing permissions and
limitations under the License.
-->
<mat-form-field appearance="fill">
  <mat-label>{{ label }}</mat-label>
  <input
    type="text"
    [placeholder]="placeholder"
    [attr.aria-label]="label"
    matInput
    [formControl]="myControl"
    [matAutocomplete]="auto"
  />
  <mat-autocomplete #auto="matAutocomplete">
    <mat-option *ngFor="let option of options" [value]="option">
      {{ option }}
    </mat-option>
  </mat-autocomplete>
</mat-form-field>

<mat-sidenav-container class="sidenav-container">
  <mat-sidenav
    class="sidenav"
    [mode]="sidenavMode"
    [opened]="sidenavOpened"
    role="navigation"
  >
    <ng-content select="[watt-shell-sidenav]"></ng-content>
  </mat-sidenav>

  <mat-sidenav-content>
    <mat-toolbar>
      <ng-content select="[watt-shell-toolbar]"></ng-content>
    </mat-toolbar>

    <main class="main-content">
      <ng-content></ng-content>
    </main>
  </mat-sidenav-content>
</mat-sidenav-container>

    lineHeight: '27px*',

    name: 'Body (text-m)',

  },

    name: 'Button',
    html: typographyHtmlSnippets.button.storybook,
    size: '16px',

    size: '12px',
